{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-03510/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-03510"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:35:10"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman speaks."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03510/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-03510","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03510/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-03510"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03510/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03510/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03510/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03510/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03510/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03510/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03510/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03510/canvas/1/7f1ea69f-b4b1-4f2e-92a4-79e3f3aed6a2","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T15:58:08.103Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Technical consultant Joan Emily Brown, who plays head seamstress Nana in the film and who worked for Hardy Amies’s fashion house, reports in an <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW77403882 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.bbc.com/culture/article/20180306-fact-v-fiction-what-phantom-thread-gets-right-and-wrong\"><u>interview</u></a> that Amies collaborated closely with his sister, Rosemary, in his enterpriseand that the latter even interviewed her for the job (“Fact v Fiction”). This dynamic is echoed in <em>Phantom Thead</em>, and PTA mentions in press materials for the film that it was something that caught his attention in his research (“<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW77403882 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.focusfeatures.com/article/background_phantom-thread_-fashion-designers\"><u>The Haute Couture World of Phantom Thread</u></a>”). Another designer, Norman Hartnell, also received financial and business support from his sister, Phyllis (“<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW77403882 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.focusfeatures.com/article/background_phantom-thread_-fashion-designers\"><u>The Haute Couture World of Phantom Thread</u></a>”).</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03510/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:622.7725437415882,171.11709286675645,714.5087483176312,701.5881561238224"}}}]}]}]}